						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēśarivarman, Year 26 = c. 10th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">Tiruvādirai-gaṇapperumakkaḷ</hi> at Tiruchcheṅgōḍu for feeding with the interest thereon five Brahmanas. Kāḍan Pudi-māṇikkan made the gift for the merit of his daughter Muṇḍaṅkōn.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIX No. 426.]</p>						

